name: Bristol's Rainshine, Millenium Part 2: Planetarium @Bristol
description: The Planetarium at Millenium Square was an absolute highlight of my visits to @Bristol science centre (now, ‘We the Curious’) when I was a child. The whole experience from leaving the general exhibits and going through the dangly tube lights, and finally into the domed theatre to be dazzled with the magnificence of astronomy and the natural world above our heads was wonderful. | 2414x3862px | f/7.1, 1/640s, 50mm | Canon 400D and Lightroom | Photographed 2nd June 2021 on a walk around the harbourside with Julia.
